Key Match Events: MacKenzie Gore delivered a stellar performance with 6.0 scoreless innings, allowing only three hits and one walk, and striking out nine Phillies batters.
James Wood hit a 2-run homer and a lead-off triple, contributing significantly to the Nationals' victory.
Joey Gallo hit a 3-run homer, adding crucial runs to secure the win.
Trea Turner hit a game-tying 2-run homer for the Phillies.
Pre-Game Insights: The Nationals were slight underdogs at +130 to win on the moneyline.
Nats' manager Dave Martinez went to his 'A' bullpen to close out the win with Derek Law, Jose A. Ferrer, and Kyle Finnegan.
Post-Match Reflections: Manager Dave Martinez praised MacKenzie Gore, saying, 'Here’s a guy who can win 18-20 games for us. When he’s in the strike zone, he’s really good. Today, he proved that.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Nationals' starting pitchers have a combined ERA of 4.36, ranking 21st in MLB.
The Nationals' top players on the FanGraphs’ WAR leaderboard are MacKenzie Gore at 3.2, Luis Garcia Jr. at 2.9, and Jacob Young at 2.6.
